5. IMMUTABLE PROOF CHAIN
Every GIOP file ends with a SHA3-512 hash. A single constant change
produces a hash mismatch that forces a version branch. Files are never
deleted; the header SUPERSEDED_BY points to the replacement.

6. VERSIONING
MAJOR: incompatible mathematical change.
MINOR: addition of a new camera body, lens profile, or display model.
PATCH: typographical correction with zero mathematical impact.

